2026-07-02 01:59:32,186 | INFO | rag_app_2026-07-02_01-57-45 | ASSISTANT: LibreOffice 7.6 was officially released on August 21, 2023, as a major version of the open-source office suite with several new features and enhancements:
- Support for zoom gestures on touchpads in the main view.
- New document themes and import/export functionality for ODF and OOXML documents.
- Improved font handling, especially for right-to-left scripts, CJK, and Asian alphabets.
- Enhancements to LibreOffice Writer, including a new Page Number Wizard and improved Paragraph Style dropdown.

LibreOffice 7.6 will be supported until June 12th, 2024. For users currently on version 7.5, it is recommended to upgrade to 7.6 as soon as the next minor update (7.6.3) is released in mid-November 2023.

Geany 2.0, an open-source Integrated Development Environment (IDE), was also released around this time:
- Experimental support for Meson build system.
- New "Change history" feature in the editor.
- Support for AutoIt and GDScript file types.
- Dark-themed friendly color support for compiler messages.
- Various UI improvements such as a new tree view, improved symbol tree filtering, and more.

For detailed changelogs and installation instructions, you can refer to the respective project's GitHub page.
